					<head>Kashkūl by Kalīm Allah</head>
					<msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85024485 https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008112367">
						<summary>A general work on the principles of Sufi teaching and practice, started (f. 2r) on 1 Zu 'l-Qaʻdah 1101 (6 August 1690) by Kalīm Allāh of the Chishtī sect. The work contains a preface, 2 sections (<term xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">vaṣl</term>) and a conclusion. </summary>
						<msItem>
							<author key="Viaf_298270316">
								<persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Kalīm Allah</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="fa">کلیم الله</persName>
							</author>
							<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_10403">Kashkūl</title>
							<title xml:lang="fa">کشکول</title>
							<incipit xml:lang="fa">الحمد لله به علیه و الصلوة من لدیه الیه. اما بعد کشکولی که لقماتش لطیفه زبانی را قوت بخشد و الخ.</incipit>
							<explicit xml:lang="fa"> و اگر اشاره میشود از ذکر آن چاره نیست. </explicit>
							<colophon xml:lang="fa">به فضلش اتمام یافت ۲۴ ذیحجه سنه ۱۱۴۶ به خط احقر العباد عبدلرحیم روز پنجشنبه</colophon>
							<colophon xml:lang="en">Copy completed by <persName role="scr" key="person_f7027">ʻAbd al-Raḥīm</persName> on Thursday <date calendar="Hijri qamari">24 ̲Zī-Ḥijjah 1146</date> (28 March 1734). The scribe may possibly be the same scribe who copied Delhi Persian 1179 at Shahjahanabad between 1734 and 1739. </colophon>
							<note>
								<p>The author is most probably to be identified with <persName key="person_f7206">Kalīm Allāh ibn Sibghat Allāh</persName>, the author of Delhi Persian 1067a. </p>
								<p>The title is given incorrectly on the flyleaf as <title>Kanz al-ʻirfān</title>. </p>
							</note>
							<textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
							<filiation>For another copy in the British Library see Delhi Persian 1067b. </filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
